&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Progression, Qualification and Professional Body&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This standard has been designed to meet the professional standards of the relevant professional bodies of the Engineering Council. &#160;On completion of the standard the Engineering Technician will be eligible to apply for registration as an Engineering Technician with a relevant professional body. &#160;On achievement of the standard, candidates will have the opportunity to progress to Master Technician, management or to develop in their current role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sta&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;nd&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;a&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;rd review&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The apprenticeship should be reviewed after 3 years&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;T&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;h&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;i&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;s apprenticeship is set at level 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
